{"title":"EcoTT PAUTA-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/EcoTT PAUTA-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"","guid":"GBV1h13aRVNNlspYkCUUWg","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"1. Preparación del paciente para\\NEcocardiograma Transtorácico (ETT)","guid":"EbulsizyB3R4X5HF13uezA","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"1.1 Posición\\Ndel paciente:","guid":"7B0BgDeGYvCoYPGjJGJ2NA","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"Decúbito lateral izquierdo (↪ facilita alineación del eje largo del corazón).","guid":"avm9jXjHNUYTEU3NMdOTGQ","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"Alineación adecuada del tórax con el transductor para mejorar calidad imagenológica.","guid":"zPmYk8zNn5zjDcBb1m1V1A","children":[]}]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"1.2 Colocación del\\Ntransductor:","guid":"PhBmtWq1g7xYsVFxbpoduQ","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"Frecuencia del transductor: Utilizar un\\Ntransductor de 2.5 - 5 MHz para adultos.","guid":"i_b2Fnoc4EjrPcB6PkWdCQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"1.3 Electrodos\\Npara ECG:","guid":"_Bd3KFLRpc5AC3OpyoPsdA","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"Colocar electrodos (si es necesario) para sincronización electrocardiográfica,\\Nespecialmente en mediciones de FE (Fracción de Eyección).","guid":"ePGDBBdFiB7CVV2Bw-9txw","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"1.4 Revisión de\\Nsignos vitales:","guid":"6025tW8lwDxbqcN65nSJ7A","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"Frecuencia cardíaca (FC) y tensión arterial (TA) deben\\Nregistrarse para correlación con datos hemodinámicos.","guid":"baXtDv98m8GH09dw9fQGcQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"1","text":"1.5 Evaluación inicial\\Nde imágenes:","guid":"sqKT0Gk9vSlkCuzO06plfA","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"Obtener imágenes preliminares para asegurar correcta orientación\\Ny visualización de estructuras cardíacas.","guid":"WCrxaEd_0r9eshJRO36_Kw","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"1","text":"1.6 Instrucciones\\Nal paciente:","guid":"etsuars6X4KtOSGIGhwjeg","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"Pedir que mantenga la respiración en ciertos momentos ↪ mejora la estabilidad de la imagen.","guid":"onJMtjYO1dl5tMVvE4MFmA","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"Ajustar el volumen de gel y presión sobre el tórax ↪ evita molestias.","guid":"grs1oDl2YrDyUqyn4llaWg","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"1","text":"1.7 Calibración\\Ndel equipo:","guid":"Sq01OI_4KHpcTz2SfNwtIg","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"Ajuste de ganancia y filtros para mejorar visualización de estructuras y reducir artefactos.","guid":"qhMZah-MK7PU7oHgKBIqDA","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"16","text":"Verificar la calidad de las imágenes en modo 2D, modo M y Doppler.","guid":"L2uVv_gZRUZNTFpHP8dYFQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"19","parent":"0","text":"2. Vista paraesternal larga (PSL) en\\NEcocardiograma Transtorácico (ETT)","guid":"hcQX7TBBQw_A5pJ2DzuyeA","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"2.1 Posición del\\Ntransductor:","guid":"XGJv-ZdxJlUeE2gpiY00Ng","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"Transductor ubicado en el 3er-4to espacio\\Nintercostal izquierdo, línea paraesternal.","guid":"DSCOqGzdqa_c_V7OYUmACg","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"Ángulo hacia el hombro derecho ↪\\Nalineación del eje largo del corazón.","guid":"w7MJtSOnVW3BJm_zb4nsMA","children":[]}]},{"id":"23","parent":"19","text":"2.2 Evaluación del\\Nventrículo izquierdo (VI):","guid":"s6dNmDrpLSv6GARJ4UniIQ","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"Medir diámetros internos del\\Nventrículo en diástole y sístole:","guid":"Q0ZT7smTDkTaGPCevTVWbA","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"Diámetro diastólico VI (DVId): ↪ Normal: 4.2 - 5.8 cm.","guid":"WJtdBcaWzSHkrkzMEZ5TEA","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"Diámetro sistólico VI (DVIs).","guid":"GjUd3r4pql_5MnLOKU9hqA","children":[]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"23","text":"Grosor de paredes: Septum interventricular (SIVd) y pared posterior (PPVId) ↪ Normal: 0.6 - 1.1 cm.","guid":"1GU_uI1lGwgXf9rRo4CEtw","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"23","text":"Calcular volúmenes: VfinD y VfinS usando método de Teichholz o Simpson biplano.","guid":"oMw_vU2_gUcaXBl1kw3mPw","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"19","text":"2.3 Evaluación\\Nde la aorta:","guid":"1UrA7DMT-FZW85xlStkggg","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"Medir diámetro de la aorta ascendente (Ao asc) ↪ Normal: 2 - 3.7 cm.","guid":"_tPooP58XiaM29FmdVfC-g","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"Evaluar válvula aórtica:","guid":"q6eIaXqnMK_3n0XC_oDZ_Q","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"Identificar número de velos ↪ Habitualmente 3.","guid":"_fBDlJm65dMqJLtvtl_q8Q","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"31","text":"Evaluar apertura (amplitud y velocidad).","guid":"HADR4N75LTWy2Q_WPWMVXA","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"31","text":"Detectar presencia de regurgitación aórtica mediante Doppler color.","guid":"BOvyBzCFo3iHr1x7XqxjfA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"35","parent":"19","text":"2.4 Evaluación de la\\Naurícula izquierda (AI):","guid":"sOXU5vdvqvbB6zhGdg8i0w","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"Medir diámetro anteroposterior de la AI (Diam AI) ↪ Normal: 2.7 - 4. 0 cm.","guid":"yCezXeYxiodTjdUYbP3UVA","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"35","text":"Área auricular: ↪ se utiliza para cálculo de volumen y función auricular.","guid":"BVhPheeShg2cTgUil9sIZw","children":[]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"19","text":"2.5 Modo M en PSL:","guid":"JWMblQjDIzgUMI1zijkPnQ","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"Medir movimiento de paredes VI ↪ permite calcular función sistólica (%FA) y\\Ndeterminar alteraciones en la motilidad global y segmentaria.","guid":"5hYKyzwMf5qZwG6L2CDXhg","children":[]}]},{"id":"40","parent":"19","text":"2.6 Imágenes adicionales:","guid":"47QsjPwW9wEIZOxKy8D6zQ","children":[{"id":"41","parent":"40","text":"Asegurar que las imágenes obtenidas en PSL sean representativas\\Ny repetir si es necesario para obtener mediciones precisas.","guid":"eb4BtDZoxLogv1X-qQ4NEw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"0","text":"3. Vista paraesternal corta (PSC) en\\NEcocardiograma Transtorácico (ETT)","guid":"J3Z07m_V4XnCh7CqG9FTVw","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"3.1 Posición del\\Ntransductor:","guid":"eGx9-LA4QqQbMaiBwQnqNg","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"Transductor en la misma ubicación de PSL (3er-4to espacio intercostal izquierdo),\\Nrotando 90° en sentido horario.","guid":"4SIzzANZayfld2Woibm5jQ","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"43","text":"Permite visualizar el eje corto de varias estructuras cardíacas a diferentes niveles.","guid":"y2NAXtaWsfXz3gkfkvNrtA","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"42","text":"3.2 Evaluación del\\Nventrículo izquierdo (VI):","guid":"vyc_QGYeM0K7__pTSfDoug","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"Medir la motilidad segmentaria del VI ↪ se evalúan segmentos basales, medios y apicales.","guid":"qFgUDk6Jd22QoJPsiM535g","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"46","text":"Analizar el espesor de la pared\\Nventricular durante sístole y diástole:","guid":"UKlfbEC_BflokfAAjxlRAg","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"Hipocinesia, acinesia o discinesia indican disfunción segmentaria.","guid":"1bXiTVxpAe0d75hSvbx_Sg","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"48","text":"Asegurar la simetría del VI ↪ alteraciones pueden sugerir remodelado o hipertrofia.","guid":"UzDD9BN1zjgF1ULoR9VPkA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"42","text":"3.3 Evaluación de la\\Nválvula aórtica (VA):","guid":"KdXXJBWSUkP5pXf-SEwUHQ","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"Vista en corte transversal de la válvula aórtica ↪ permite observar los 3 velos.","guid":"DtBML0Nr1IIEz-BuBeZMng","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"51","text":"Medir la apertura de los velos ↪ amplitud de apertura correlaciona con el área valvular.","guid":"WcKao6wssa7pZInM5hVK3w","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"51","text":"Evaluar la presencia de estenosis o insuficiencia aórtica con Doppler color.","guid":"9C6Hbazrca43JfaFV8oNzg","children":[]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"42","text":"3.4 Evaluación de la\\Nválvula mitral (VM):","guid":"p72rvvVGJtacNLeSCk0z2g","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"Vista de la mitral en corte transversal en el plano basal ↪ permite observar la apertura de los velos anterior y posterior.","guid":"8bMxzqZLkHZIWWqLyBZKlg","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"55","text":"Evaluar la función valvular (apertura conservada o limitada).","guid":"HGu9lb_kWoluQ0_en16tAg","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"55","text":"Verificar la presencia de insuficiencia mitral mediante Doppler color.","guid":"Q5AX44HPb0qHcKYi884y0A","children":[]}]},{"id":"59","parent":"42","text":"3.5 Evaluación del tracto de salida del ventrículo\\Nderecho (VD) y válvula pulmonar (VP):","guid":"XtsKA7JOPlHqiTNTw03iRQ","children":[{"id":"60","parent":"59","text":"Evaluar el tracto de salida del VD para medir su diámetro y analizar el flujo sanguíneo.","guid":"XK6gxm6y036xzvs897j5Cw","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"59","text":"Evaluar función y apertura de la válvula pulmonar:","guid":"Ggofib9Na0To9aJfPZXawA","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"Medir el gradiente de presión pulmonar y detectar insuficiencia mediante Doppler.","guid":"Bpy6ki2KmJ-s46C-Uv9p2Q","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"42","text":"3.6 Evaluación de\\Ncavidades derechas:","guid":"19r041CTLN7I8Ck9IQ8epw","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"Visualización de la aurícula derecha (AD) y ventrículo derecho (VD).","guid":"A4NWs_pAyTOL1IEf6AdTVQ","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"63","text":"Medir el tamaño del VD en sístole y diástole ↪ útil para detectar dilatación o disfunción.","guid":"NBUxDrsbC8ApHi3d02wgzA","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"63","text":"Verificar la relación de tamaños entre cavidades derechas e izquierdas.","guid":"ZQxkiPX-enZbLsl882WH7A","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"42","text":"3.7 Doppler\\Nen PSC:","guid":"rloO12R-tOzoQhg1sfCU5Q","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Aplicar Doppler color para evaluar flujos de regurgitación o\\Nestenosis en válvulas aórtica, mitral y pulmonar.","guid":"V_E5BRL86CKEXIZ58vmlkQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"69","parent":"0","text":"4. Vista apical de 4 cámaras (A4C) en\\NEcocardiograma Transtorácico (ETT)","guid":"_dC2fcIz-EE0-Q9mLYh1pQ","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"4.1 Posición del\\Ntransductor:","guid":"PwecueWcsADJ8xtnUBnpjA","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"Transductor colocado en el ápex cardíaco, justo debajo del pectoral izquierdo.","guid":"id2MS6lopFDyuCzVGX5-yA","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"70","text":"Orientar hacia el hombro derecho ↪ alineación del eje largo del corazón.","guid":"kypdgs1dgHkB50bq-Ku6iQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"69","text":"4.2 Evaluación del\\Nventrículo izquierdo (VI):","guid":"vkaaRfoi3z70qzuqOk29wg","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Medir fracción de eyección (FE) por método de Simpson (MOD BP) ↪\\N%FA = [(VfdVI - VfsVI) / VfdVI] × 100.","guid":"xB3Rj-zGEfbVOagaiQTEvw","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"73","text":"Medir volumen telesistólico (VfsVI) y\\Nvolumen telediastólico (VfdVI):","guid":"5X04ldoEshLGVqAOYoqp0g","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"VfdVI Normal: 70-120 ml.","guid":"Fz1PgZt7sdUCNPvxEOt5Hg","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"75","text":"VfsVI Normal: 20-50 ml.","guid":"tNCXUs9SvA9yObAm_20nMg","children":[]}]},{"id":"78","parent":"73","text":"Evaluar motilidad segmentaria en 4C ↪ detectar\\Ndisfunción de segmentos basales, medios y apicales.","guid":"kIP64Xg-Yco3p8YqN06aeQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"69","text":"4.3 Evaluación del\\Nventrículo derecho (VD):","guid":"lJexh1_BAJdJNwEbve8Kzg","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":"Evaluar tamaño del VD ↪ Normal: <3.5 cm (diámetro basal).","guid":"S5apQ3IXJilDKop6slD1dQ","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"79","text":"Evaluar TAPSE (Excursión sistólica del anillo tricuspídeo) ↪ normal >1.6 cm.","guid":"LOeXo-I0zC0qHg8jBwchDg","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"79","text":"Medir onda S con Doppler tisular (evaluación de función sistólica VD).","guid":"m_P4k3KAy_OUhpXWTBSnyg","children":[]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"69","text":"4.4 Evaluación de la\\Nválvula mitral (VM):","guid":"uQ1iGUmHc1fxDk3H-f5QVg","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"Evaluar función mitral:","guid":"7VQZsrDdDoOKO2UfCMNBqg","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"83","text":"Velocidad E y A (llenado ventricular): Vel. E VM y Vel. A VM.","guid":"xclomzfNub_ak2YVDfXLPQ","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"83","text":"Calcular índice E/A ↪ normal: 1 - 2.","guid":"b1OayHG3j19bXCrfWW9deQ","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"83","text":"Medir T de desaceleración (Tdesacel VM) ↪ indica rigidez ventricular.","guid":"RGF3yEvFDg-mH2KXUL5Vog","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"83","text":"Medir E’ y E/E’ mediante Doppler tisular para evaluar función diastólica:","guid":"TI_8C8-6EAKyhbhIbArDgQ","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"83","text":"E' lat. >0.10 m/s y E/E' <8: función diastólica normal.","guid":"eEOUTIwTGI5yxY_Dz0xk7w","children":[]}]},{"id":"90","parent":"69","text":"4.5 Evaluación de la\\Nválvula tricúspide (VT):","guid":"Hfz8JtaRkRk0l5N1Xu4D6w","children":[{"id":"91","parent":"90","text":"Medir gradiente de presión en válvula tricúspide (PSAP) ↪ normal <35 mmHg.","guid":"Yi-k8g0Hi7zGdppvZGD1Fw","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"90","text":"Evaluar regurgitación tricuspídea con Doppler color.","guid":"I-z5zg3U35VNr1ikkkrqdA","children":[]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"69","text":"4.6 Evaluación de\\Naurícula izquierda (AI):","guid":"zJgsd9JxszdXoQxnSOwxxw","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Medir área auricular (A-L) y calcular volumen auricular indexado:","guid":"dcHFeaGJhEGanD5O0qzRJA","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"Volumen indexado normal: <34 ml/m².","guid":"9Aq3eSN8dXRZwhdi5vk2jQ","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"93","text":"Evaluar tamaño y función ↪ correlación con insuficiencia mitral o estenosis mitral.","guid":"1ZLBBZ7sLYO7nvmEXiSAqg","children":[]}]},{"id":"97","parent":"69","text":"4.7 Evaluación de\\Naurícula derecha (AD):","guid":"EurHxOqsxsgoyZfDDqZvYg","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"Medir tamaño de la AD ↪ Normal: <18 cm².","guid":"oMAaB6siRG0QGulaP8dBeg","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"Evaluar posibles dilataciones ↪ indican disfunción derecha o hipertensión pulmonar.","guid":"5Tl1WF6GMaawpD2MC6J8AQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"69","text":"4.8 Evaluación\\Ncon Doppler:","guid":"4hzXFqZQC0xkkr4JuccoAg","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"Usar Doppler color para evaluar flujos de regurgitación en válvulas mitral y tricúspide.","guid":"6rIK_OiZiabUdaYtoAT0sQ","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"Medir velocidad y gradientes en válvulas para determinar la severidad de estenosis o insuficiencia.","guid":"kaTCPWA4YK0wb5XAsqHalQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"103","parent":"0","text":"5. Doppler pulsado y color en\\NEcocardiograma Transtorácico (ETT)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"104","parent":"103","text":"5.1 Doppler\\Npulsado (DP):","guid":"tTypmW_Gr3l4C4pXukVBNg","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"Utilizado para medir la velocidad del flujo sanguíneo a través de las válvulas cardíacas y cavidades.","guid":"SaG7GZLW5uHDWKKL-pluZA","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"104","text":"Colocar volumen de muestra en los puntos de interés:","guid":"f3O-EuHQN4TUjjUZvPCJQw","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"104","text":"Válvula mitral (VM) ↪ evaluar llenado ventricular.","guid":"SUwicAB6i7O3m9LcnMs8Vw","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"104","text":"Válvula tricúspide (VT) ↪ medir presión sistólica pulmonar.","guid":"I0FfKM2zlJDt7riJhbTBXA","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"104","text":"Válvula aórtica (VA) ↪ calcular gradientes de presión.","guid":"SsmegnIUAsRSZg0FrdDS1w","children":[]}]},{"id":"110","parent":"103","text":"5.2 Doppler\\Ncolor:","guid":"zm15AUT5LARs--BgCTYSog","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"Muestra los flujos\\Nsanguíneos en color:","guid":"lCJba34VvCVBfuf7_0dNOw","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"Rojo: flujo hacia el transductor.","guid":"COfH28E1GrRKTt8v2eSxRA","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"Azul: flujo alejándose del transductor.","guid":"d779G6VaBIpfKJVK8iYXdg","children":[]}]},{"id":"114","parent":"110","text":"Utilizado para identificar regurgitación o estenosis en las válvulas.","guid":"3x-TX8WrTm8XhOM3flAOgQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"103","text":"5.3 Doppler en\\Nválvula mitral (VM):","guid":"qo9ADkuirFbOvSKs6vnchw","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"Medir velocidad del\\Nflujo diastólico:","guid":"q3N-ReCrhPUe446qwrKauQ","children":[{"id":"117","parent":"116","text":"Vel. E (onda de llenado rápido) ↪ normal: 0.6-1.3 m/s.","guid":"zQzsIZaifaSjx7kV4bVl7w","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"116","text":"Vel. A (onda de contracción auricular) ↪ normal: 0.2-0.7 m/s.","guid":"oCE2xhZ2lCyhI-eGdi5XOQ","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"116","text":"Calcular índice E/A ↪ normal: 1-2.","guid":"tRFH-faDgPhevDrxlpaieA","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"116","text":"Medir tiempo de desaceleración (Tdesacel VM) ↪ normal: 150-220 ms.","guid":"VZXvum5ErrhFRC9OkEOFYg","children":[]}]},{"id":"121","parent":"115","text":"Medir E' (velocidad del anillo mitral)\\Nmediante Doppler tisular:","guid":"LNjVpYymbRwmW5B22-YoXw","children":[{"id":"122","parent":"121","text":"E' tabique: Normal >0.08 m/s.","guid":"wp3zvb8douIuzA6g4QlNkg","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"121","text":"E' lateral: Normal >0.10 m/s.","guid":"1tIjvRh2DqQQSxpbGeTtKg","children":[]}]},{"id":"124","parent":"115","text":"Calcular el índice E/E' para evaluar la\\Npresión de llenado ventricular izquierdo:","guid":"PFlbeUeWFSALJ4QvYXmL0A","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"E/E' <8: Normal.","guid":"rZZXX45TryXJn5cDAbdwwQ","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"124","text":"E/E' >15: Elevada presión de llenado.","guid":"Ksuv76QZ33LLdv9rNLCubw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"127","parent":"103","text":"5.4 Doppler en válvula\\Ntricúspide (VT):","guid":"04d_lcl_jtLblPW-wQovYg","children":[{"id":"128","parent":"127","text":"Medir la velocidad máxima de la regurgitación tricuspídea ↪ Vmax VT.","guid":"-tslGOrqyrvVdiBsf_TrRQ","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"127","text":"Estimar la presión sistólica\\Narterial pulmonar (PSAP):","guid":"12K7-XSX8pKPGxtG1TLxSA","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"Normal: <35 mmHg.","guid":"kdmatBN688kjAjtNW3qMDA","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"PSAP = 4 × (Vmax VT)² + presión aurícula derecha.","guid":"RMur4cmJkGyUfQFOeBj2MQ","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"Evaluar la onda S en Doppler tisular para analizar función sistólica del VD.","guid":"NUpUzPd4h4X85doTMnttsQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"103","text":"5.5 Doppler en\\Nválvula aórtica (VA):","guid":"RkU9vJ2mYGRPP3AUBjutbg","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"Medir la velocidad máxima del flujo aórtico (Vmax VA) ↪ Normal: 1-2 m/s.","guid":"e0nRuOPNbXfvueh1OzPG5A","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"Calcular el gradiente de\\Npresión máximo y medio:","guid":"nw3-k6vA0mfpDSLFQaHs4A","children":[{"id":"136","parent":"135","text":"GPmáx: <16 mmHg.","guid":"8VJnypsSY6AovJNUWcZ3vw","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"135","text":"GPmedia: <10 mmHg.","guid":"X4vHL4pnjPP0160B5XZTUA","children":[]}]},{"id":"138","parent":"133","text":"Evaluar índice\\Ntiempo-velocidad (VTI):","guid":"1we7k-YZ45fLeQEMYcgwSQ","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"Relacionado con el volumen sistólico.","guid":"CZk3F1bNyZBpsD-jcG51lQ","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"138","text":"VTI normal: 18-24 cm.","guid":"gW2UVZ